<TITLE> Road accidents kill 4 in two districts </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 13 (bdnews24.com) -- Four people died in road accidents in Narayanganj and Tangail Tuesday and Wednesday, police said. The bdnews24.com Narayanganj correspondent said a truck loaded with flour turned turtle on Dhaka-Chittagong highway near Kanchpur Tuesday night. While the truck veered and hurtled off the highway, the loosened flour sacks fell over a group of people waiting on the roadside. Three garments workers died instantly and seven others suffered injuries. Sonargaon police failed to identify the dead. Motaleb Hossain, sub-inspector of Tangail Police Station, said a Sharishabari-bound truck lost control at Bhatkura, ran over a pedestrian Muslim Uddin, 27, and fell into a roadside ditch. Muslim Uddin died on the spot. He was a factory worker at Universal Yarn Limited of the local BISIC Shilpa Nagari. The bdnews24.com Tangail correspondent said Muslim Uddin came from Narunda in Sadar upazila. bdnews
